This memorandum, issued by President Donald J. Trump on November 12, 2019, delegates the authority to the Federal Labor Relations Authority (FLRA) to remove the Chairman and any other member of the Federal Service Impasses Panel (FSIP). The FLRA is instructed to consider the consistency of the FSIP members' decisions with the requirements of Chapter 71 of title 5, United States Code, particularly in relation to an effective and efficient government. Within 10 days of exercising this authority, the FLRA must submit a report to the President explaining the reasons for its action. The memorandum also includes general provisions stating that it does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It emphasizes that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party. The FLRA is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.